SIMPLE: wander
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wander
<hw>Wan"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Wandered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Wandering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wandren</ets>, <ets>wandrien</ets>, AS. <ets>wandrian</ets>; akin
to G. <ets>wandern</ets> to wander; fr. AS. <ets>windan</ets> to turn.
See <er>Wind</er> to turn.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To ramble here and there without any certain course
or with no definite object in view; to range about; to stroll; to rove;
<as>as, to <ex>wander</ex> over the fields</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>wandered</qex> about in sheepskins and goatskins.</q>
<rj><qau>Heb. xi. 37.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>wandereth</qex> abroad for bread.</q> <rj><qau>Job xv.
23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To go away; to depart; to stray off; to deviate; to
go astray; <as>as, a writer <ex>wanders</ex> from his
subject</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When God caused me to <qex>wander</qex> from my father's
house.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xx. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, let me not <qex>wander</qex> from thy commandments.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cxix. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be delirious; not to be under the guidance of
reason; to rave; <as>as, the mind <ex>wanders</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To roam; rove; range; stroll; gad; stray;
straggly; err; swerve; deviate; depart.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wander</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wander
<hw>Wan"der</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To travel over without a certain
course; to traverse; to stroll through.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧[Elijah] <xex>wandered</xex> this barren waste.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wanderer</ent>⟦br⟧
